    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Acer saccharinum, native to eastern North America and widely cultivated elsewhere. It is a soft wood, used for crating and inexpensive furniture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
